        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:22PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southeast of Alma, moving northeast at 70 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Jethro...                         Alma...
Shibley...                        Cass...
Dyer...                           Kibler...
Bidville...                       Mountainburg...
Crosses...                        Combs...
Locke...                          Turners Bend...
Mount Gayler...                   Lonelm...
Dutton...                         Wyola...
Mulberry...                       Barnes...
Pettigrew...                      St. Paul...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 8 and 29.
Interstate 540 near mile marker 2.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 34.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
